HEADWORD: Nipplewort
<hw>Nip"ple*wort`</hw> <pr>(n⟦icr⟧p"p'l*w⟦ucir⟧rt`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A yellow-flowered composite herb (<spn>Lampsana
communis</spn>), formerly used as an external application to the nipples
of women; -- called also <altname>dock-cress</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nipponese</ent>⟦br⟧
